@node "Welcome" "Welcome to Amiga Information Online"
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                          Editorial By Chris Seward
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

 Hello once again, yes we are back! no doubt about that, we battle on and
bring you another exciting issue of AIO. This issue is slightly smaller
than regular issues have been recently but there is no quality loss what
so ever. Lee Hesselden has been working fingers to the bone this month
to bring you another great selection of the latest games reviews... well
actually I tell a lie, he has had a bit of a break this month after doing
alot of the reviews for last issue which just missed the deadline. Two
major disappointments this month is that we could not bring you the reviews
of Quake or Genetic Species. We could have brought you the review of Quake 
but we are going to save it til next month so we can review both games
in the same issue and then put them head2head. The problem has been with
Genetic Species and that we could not get any sound from the game but i'm
having words with Paul Carrington at Vulcan and it'll be sorted in time
for next issue.

 Another exciting article this month is about the very nearly here BSE98
party in belgium, its a party for any scener to go along and make demos,
music, do graphics and other sceney things. Check out the news section
for the full invitation. We see a new web browser comming to the Amiga,
PCx and Fusion drop in price and many other great news storys.

 One big @{b}PLEA@{ub} this month is for more contributors and suggestions,
so if you can help with AIO in two major positions being Co-Editor and
Utils Editor then we want to hear from you ASAP. If you want to see a
review of your game/util or an article or help section started then get
in touch with us and let us know about it.

 The last bit of news I have to tell you is AIO now has its own UK helpline
the number is a mobile phone number and can be called at any time. If you 
need help with anything or would like to give your ideas or comments then 
please do phone us. It is also possible to register as an official AIO 
reader via phone by giving the details of what the printed form states. 
If the phone is unavailble please leave contact details or just read out 
the registration details and we'll get back to you. So if you need to get 
in touch just phone : @{b}0831 37 09 22@{ub} - 24 hours a day every day of the year.

 Well for the 14th issue I say goodbye and would like to thankyou for
supporting AIO. See you the same place next month?

                            @{b}aio@freedom.usa.com@{ub}

