@node "gr3" "TCAA"

@{fg shine} T.V Chubbies in Armchair Assassin@{fg text}

 This game is based on the very loveable T.V Chubbies (Known to us in the
U.K as the BBC`s newest stars in the British Children`s lives, these
characters will, however, remain nameless!)

 You play on an arena approxamtely 4 screens big, there are various options
available at the start of each game you play. You can choose how many
Chubbies come out of their little box, their speed, your weapon, and you
can even change the look of the screen, to make it a kind of white snowy
look!

 The idea is to blow the living daylights out of the Chubbies, in the
quickest possible time, the time is actually a bit of a con because, as the
number of Chubbies you start with is reduced, the rate at which the counter
ticks over is increased to compensate.

 The game itself isn`t brilliant in the lastablity section, amusingly
titled "Revenge-Ware", the whole point of the game is to get rid of some of
your anger, and blast the little bliters to the death!

 Now for the technical bit... You may need some fast RAM to play T.V
Chubbies properly, when you have the maxium number of Chubbies running
round the screen, on a standard A1200 the game slows down! I have also
noticed, that the high score table only saves the last 3 digits from the
clock, this means if the clock stops on 1001 you come first with 1 on the
