@node "ur1" "WBJoyTest V1.11"

@{fg shine} WBJoyTest V1.11@{fg text}

 WBJoyTest V1.11 is a simple program to test to see if your joysticks
are working correctly. If you are playing a game and find that movement
is stiff on one direction or there is no movement at all load up
WBjtv1.11 and you can test it out to see if it is the games fault or if
your joystick is really knackered.

 Its small, its simple and its fast, it gets the job it is supposed to
do done quickly and easily. Although the main file is a bit big at 48k
it is still a very useful program. The best feature about WBjtv1.11 is
that depending on what direction you move the joystick the button telling
you which way you moved is pressed in and a different sample is played
for each direction. You can change the samples a customise it to your
own samples. The program comes with drum, symbol and snare samples but
you could change them to your favourite samples say like the simpsons
with homers 'doh!' and other noises.

 Overall a great little program that can be customised galore, maybe
the main program is a bit on the big size for what the program does but
a very useful program and one that everyone needs to get hold of,
especially after a couple of hours joystick bashing on SWOS!

