@node "ur3" "SSClock"

@{fg shine} SSClock (Sampled Speaking Clock)@{fg text}

 SSClock, which stands for Sampled Speaking Clock (original name, huh?)
is a speaking clock if you hadn't already realised by the title of it.
You click on the blitz basic icon and it speaks you the time. It is
actually very good compared to other programs of this nature. Most other
speaking clocks on the amiga are jerky and the samples are not flowing
so you can tell that the times and hours have been stuck together but with
SSClock it seems as if everything has been said in one go for each
individual time.

 Its a good program and the most interesting feature is you can use your
own voice or anyones voice if you have access to a sampler. The program
comes with three pre-recored voices. One is by Gareth Murfin himself in
the geordy accent (newcastle area for people who don't live in the UK)
the second is Steve Clack and some woman speaking the time together
and the last is in a Canadian accent by some canadian bloke.

 Overall its a nice simple program with much customisation to be made to
it. You don't have big gaps in-between the different numbers so it sounds
good and with your own voice you can impress you friends. 

@{b}Available from@{ub}: Aminet util/boot
@{b}Archived name@{ub} : ssclock.lha

Overall 86% out of 100% 

@{b}Reviewed by@{ub}   : Chris Seward

    @{" Main Menu " link "Main" } @{" Utils Menu " link "Util" }
@endnode

@node "ur4" "MDoodle"

@{fg shine} Mdoodle - WB doodler@{fg text}

 MDoodle is a small workbench program to let you draw in a wb window,
you can have the window any size you want and the drawing area as big
as you want. There are various options and different shapes and colours
you can use. You can change the draw colour, the background colour and
the different drawing tools from simple line draw to circles, triangles,
thick lines and sprays. 

 This small program reminds me of the old childrens game Magnadoodle
where you had two knobs that you could twist to draw different things
and then shake it to erase the picture, just think of Mdoodle as a
90's version of the old childrens game. I don't actually know what
the 'm' in MDoodle stands for, i'd guess it is Magna but the authors
name is Mark so it could also maybe stand for MarkDoodle. Well its not
the name that counts but the program.

 Overall a nice wb game but the lifespan will leave something to be
desired. Maybe in the far distant future this could turn into something
more complicated and be a WB paint package, who knows?

@{b}Available from@{ub}: Aminet wb/???
@{b}Archived name@{ub} : mdoodle.lha

Overall 73% out of 100% 

@{b}Reviewed by@{ub}   : Chris Seward

