@node "us" "Utils Scores"

@{fg shine} Utils reviews and what there score means@{fg text}

 Utils are not marked on how good they are compared to other utils,
they are marked by usefulness and what purpose they serve. As there
are so many different utils that do so many different things it is
hard to review something like MUI and then when reviewing a program
like a WB clock say it wasn't up to the standard of MUI. This is why
it is not possible to have a Top Ten list for utils.

 90%+    -  AIO GOLD (amazing)

 70-89%  -  Great but lacking some features

 50-69%  -  Not to good but it'll do

 30-49%  -  Hasn't really been thought out to well

 0-29%   -  POOR! AVOID!

    @{" Main Menu " link "Main" } @{" Utils Menu " link "Util" }
@endnode

@node "fe1" "AIO

@{fg shine} AIO needs your help@{fg text}

 AIO has now been running for 1 year and 2 months, it has been hard work
to get to how it is now and a small group of people have put alot of
effort into keeping this magazine running. The reason I am writing this
article is to hopefully get you readers to chip in a bit and help out.
AIO is not like main stream magazines like Amiga Format or CUAmiga, running
AIO is not my job, i do not get paid and there is no sponsership to
fund the running of it. So all in all I make AIO off my own back and
out of my own pocket. I give great thanks to the people who have helped
over this time like Daniel Kittingan and Adrian Hendy who sadly are
not editors any more but contributed regularly in past issues. Now the
job is down to me as main editor and the games editor, Lee Hesselden. As
you can probably see the newest issues are much better than issues 1,2 and
any of the other earlier issues and that is because I have more staff
helping out, but now there is only the two of us working on the magazine
and the less people helping out the more the standard of the magazine
will drop.

 So what I am asking is a bit of support or help. I am currently looking
for a Deputy Editor and a Games Editor, if you think you can regularly
help out in one of those spaces please get in touch. If not you can
still contribute a small review or article now and again. It isn't that
much bother to write one article or a help guide.

 I am not about to stop AIO any time soon but in future it may come to
the crunch that it will have to stop. No support unfortunally equals
no magazine. So contribute now and stop AIO comming to an end.

    @{" Main Menu " link "Main" } @{" Articles Menu " link "arti" }
@endnode

